    ourValue.textContent = "Russia";
    ourValueInfo.textContent = "Russia - Russia (Russian Federation) - the largest state in the world, which occupies 1/6 of the entire land area of the Earth. It is a country with a long history, rich culture and generous nature. Some architectural and historical and cultural monuments on the territory of the Russian Federation are included in the list of UNESCO World Heritage Sites. Russia is the homeland of great poets and writers, artists and architects, scientists, musicians, composers, cosmonauts and travelers. Russian painting, classical music and ballet are part of the world cultural heritage. Russia is located in the Northern Hemisphere, in the north of the Eurasia continent. Conventionally, the borders between Europe and Asia run along the Ural Mountains, the Ural River and the Caspian Sea, therefore part of the country is located in Europe, part in Asia. Russia shares borders with eighteen countries. It has land borders with Norway, Finland, Estonia, Latvia, Lithuania, Poland, Belarus, Ukraine, Abkhazia, Georgia, South Ossetia, Azerbaijan, Kazakhstan, China, Mongolia and North Korea. Sea borders - with Japan and the USA. The climate of Central Russia is characterized by slight temperature differences. In winter, the average temperature here is -10 ° С, and in summer - + 20 ° С. In Western Siberia, in winter, the air temperature can drop to -40 ° С, and in summer, on average, + 20 ° С. The lowest temperatures are in Eastern Siberia. In the village of Oymyakon in Yakutia, the lowest temperature was noted (-72 ° C). In summer, it is cool and humid here, the average temperature is + 19 ° С.";
    ourValue1.textContent = "Poland";
    ourValueInfo1.textContent = ` Poland is a state in Eastern Europe. It is located mostly in the Central European Plain, as well as in the northeastern part of the mountainous regions of Central Europe. From the north it is washed by the Baltic Sea. The total area of Poland is 312 658 km² (in terms of area it ranks 69th in the world and 9th in Europe). Climate. The climate of Poland is temperate, transitional from maritime to continental. Climatic conditions are influenced by colliding ocean masses from the west, cold air from Scandinavia and Russia, and warmer subtropical air from the south. Currency. Zloty (PLN). Currency can be exchanged at specialized exchange offices (Kantor wymiany walut or Kantor), no commission is charged. "Exchangers" are usually located at train stations or in the historic center of the city (as a rule, they are not in banks). Banks are open from 8:30 am to 1:00 pm on weekdays (central offices until 5:00 pm), some are open until 6:00 pm. Exchange offices usually work until 19: 00-20: 00, and even longer in large tourist centers. Credit cards are accepted in many hotels and restaurants, car rental companies, etc.`;
    ourValue2.textContent = "Turkey";
    ourValueInfo2.textContent = `Turkey is a country of ancient traditions and customs. A country of ancient cities filled with modern oriental flavor, elders in red frescoes, black-haired beauties in dresses made of beads and pearls, the smell of freshly baked bread, oriental music and dances - all this is Turkey. This country is attractive because it provides a wide variety of opportunities for active or relaxing, chic or low-budget, large company or romantic and secluded recreation. This country, which is open to guests all year round: in summer, rest on the beaches of the Mediterranean and Aegean Seas, in winter ski resorts, throughout the year - historical excursions, adventure tours, shopping. Climate and weather in Turkey Turkey's climate varies by region. In the west and south, dominated by a Mediterranean climate, the summer months are hot and dry and the winters mild. The temperature of the water and air on the Mediterranean coast allows swimming and sunbathing from April to October. But the climate of the Aegean coast is a little milder, the air temperature here is 3-5 degrees lower and the air humidity is less. The swimming season is also from April to October. Currency of Turkey The monetary unit of Turkey is the Turkish lira. Money can be exchanged everywhere, but private exchange offices usually offer better rates than banks or hotels. When exchanging, please note that the exchange office may take a commission for each operation (there should be a corresponding announcement about this).`;
    ourValue3.textContent = "Malaysia";
    ourValueInfo3.textContent = `Malaysia is an amazing country of unusual combinations, where in the capital you can find a traditional Malay village, squeezed by skyscrapers; where huge multi-colored butterflies sit on the hoods of expensive cars, and a king with a magnificent title signs bills proposed by parliament. Malaysia, which gained independence only in 1957, is today an actively developing country, the industrial sector of which makes up about half of the GDP; in second place is the sphere of services and tourism. It is curious that Malaysia is the world leader in the production of certain types of household appliances and electronics. The motley ethnic composition, friendly coexistence of different nationalities with their own traditions and customs, combined with the unique nature, make Malaysia especially attractive for tourists from all over the world. Malaysia is a federal elective constitutional monarchy, consisting of three federal territories and thirteen states, nine of which are monarchies, whose hereditary rulers (sultans) are also the spiritual heads of the states. Once every five years, they elect the Supreme Ruler of the country - the king (his title in Malay sounds like "Yang di-Pertuan Agong"), who performs representative functions. The real government of the country is in the hands of the parliament and the cabinet of ministers. Climate The country is characterized by a hot and humid equatorial climate dependent on monsoons. During the day and throughout the year, the air temperature fluctuates very slightly - from 25 ° to 28 ° C, only in lowlands, and especially river ones, can exceed 30 ° C. Air humidity in the rainy season reaches 90% - but the showers are mostly short-term (no more than two hours). On the east coast of Malacca (West Malaysia), in the west of Sarawak and in the northeast of Sabah, the rainy season is from October-November to February; on the west coast (Langkawi, Penang, Pangkor islands) - in April-May and from October to December. There are no seismically active zones on the territory of the country - this factor and temperature stability allow tourists to plan a trip to Malaysia at any time of the year. Currency The national currency of Malaysia is the ringgit (denoted as MYR); banknotes in denominations of 1, 5, 10, 20, 50 and 100 ringgit. The ringgit is divided into 100 sen - coins of 1, 5, 10, 20, 50 sen are used. Dollars, euros, British pounds sterling can be exchanged at all Malaysian commercial banks and some hotels. Banks are open on weekdays from 9:15 am to 4:30 pm (some are open until 4:00 pm). The national currency of Malaysia is the ringgit (denoted as MYR); banknotes in denominations of 1, 5, 10, 20, 50 and 100 ringgit. The ringgit is divided into 100 sen - coins of 1, 5, 10, 20, 50 sen are used. Dollars, euros, British pounds sterling can be exchanged at all Malaysian commercial banks and some hotels. Banks are open on weekdays from 9:15 am to 4:30 pm (some are open until 4:00 pm).`; 
    ourValue4.textContent = "Great Britain";
    ourValueInfo4.textContent = `Great Britain's official name is the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland - an island state in northwest Europe. It consists of four "historic provinces": England, Scotland, Wales and Northern Ireland. The state is located in the British Isles. The area of Great Britain is 243 809 km², the southern coast is connected to continental Europe through a 50 km long Eurotunnel (of which 38 km are under water). This is the longest underwater tunnel in the world. Northern Ireland shares a 360 kilometer land border with the Republic of Ireland and is the UK's only land border. The Greenwich Observatory in London is the site of the prime meridian. Climate Great Britain has a temperate oceanic climate with a lot of rainfall throughout the year. Temperatures vary with the seasons, but rarely drop below -11 ° C or rise above 35 ° C. The main winds come from the southwest and often bring cold and wet weather from the Atlantic Ocean, but the eastern parts of the country are mostly sheltered from these winds, and since most of the rainfall occurs in the western regions, the eastern ones are the driest. The Atlantic currents, warmed by the Gulf Stream, bring mild winters, sometimes snowfalls in winter and early spring, although snow usually does not last long. Currency unit Pound sterling, pound, British pound (£). £ 1 is sibdivided into 100p. You can change your currency at banks that are open Monday through Friday from 9:30 am to 3:30 pm (large banks are open until 5:30 pm), as well as at currency exchange offices, which often work around the clock. It is worthwhile to evaluate in advance the profitability of exchanging money at a bank or point, comparing the rate and commission.`;
    ourValue5.textContent = "USA";
    ourValueInfo5.textContent = `The official name is the United States of America. It is ranked third in the world in terms of territory and fourth in population. The main territory is located on the North American continent and borders in the north with Canada, in the south - with Mexico, the east coast is washed by the waters of the Atlantic Ocean, the west coast - by the Pacific Ocean. Climate The territory of the United States is unique, as all climatic zones are represented here, from the arctic in Alaska to the tropical in Hawaii. The Pacific coast is characterized by a temperate and subtropical climate, the Atlantic coast - continental-maritime. The average July temperature is +22 degrees, on the western coast +26 degrees, on the eastern and southern inner plateaus and plateaus - up to +32 degrees.`;
    ourValue6.textContent = "Canada";
    ourValueInfo6.textContent = ` Canada is a state of the British Commonwealth, and formally the head of state is the Queen of England. The Queen's official representative in Canada is the Governor General, who is appointed by the Queen on the advice of the Prime Minister. Canada is a state located in North America. Language Canada has two official languages - English and French. English is the first language of 16.1 million Canadians, and French is the first language of 6.6 million. For many Canadians, their native languages are Italian, Chinese, German, Portuguese, Polish, Ukrainian, Danish, Greek and others. Canada is the best country to live in For several years in a row, Canada has been recognized as the best country to live in by the UN Commission. The choice is made on the basis of many indicators, which include the health care system, the quality and availability of education, the cleanliness of the environment, protected by the law of individual freedoms, and the average level of wages in relation to expenses. This can only mean one thing: Canada is a country where people with high incomes live, where people are tolerant of each other, where the government provides free, but at the same time, high-quality medical care, where they provide free secondary education, and where it is good to live among friendly people. Living standards in Canada are considered one of the highest in the world. If a person agrees to work, then his future and the future of his children in Canada are guaranteed. In 1986, the World Bank estimated that every average Canadian is practically a millionaire. The average Canadian has 960,000 Canadian dollars on hand. Canada is one of the most environmentally friendly countries in the world. In Canada, you can safely drink tap water, without thinking about the consequences associated with Chernobyl or other contamination still unknown to us.`;

