    faqTitle.textContent = "What is apostille?";
    faqTitleInfo.textContent = "international standardized filling form information about the legality of the document for presentation to territories of countries that recognize this form of legalization.The Apostille stamp is placed on originals and copies of documents.";
    faqTitle1.textContent = "Where can I get an apostille?";
    faqTitleInfo1.textContent = "state bodies authorized to affix apostille in Uzbekistan,these are, first of all, various resolutions: Ministry of Justice of the Republic of Uzbekistan, Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Republic of Uzbekistan; as well as the General Executive Office Of the Republic of Uzbekistan and the State Testing Center under the Cabinet of Ministers of the Republic of Uzbekistan.";
    faqTitle2.textContent = "Why do you need an apostille?";
    faqTitleInfo2.textContent = "such a form is documented and guaranteed to confirm that your document is legal and can be used for outside the Republic of Uzbekistan.";
    faqTitle3.textContent = "What does an apostille look like?";
    faqTitleInfo3.textContent = 'the apostille form is the same in all countries: in the "cap" the document has the word "Apostille" in French,followed by the inscription “Convention de la Haye du 5 octobre 1961 "or" The Hague Convention of October 5, 1961 ".';
    faqTitle4.textContent = "Where is the apostille affixed?";
    faqTitleInfo4.textContent = "the apostille stamp can be placed as on the original document, and on its notarized copy (for example, on a birth certificate in Uzbekistan). On the original, as well as on its certified translation, this stamp necessary in cases where the feed is performed originals of documents to the countries where the certification through several instances (the so-called double apostille). Under such conditions, the applicant has to collect a much larger number of inquiries non-commercial purposes, confirming the authenticity the signatures of the person who issued them.";
    faqTitle5.textContent = "How long will the visa process take?";
    faqTitleInfo5.textContent = "The term for consideration of a package of documents for a visa is up to 8 weeks (on average 4-6) (Germany).";
    faqTitle6.textContent = "Why do you need insurance?";
    faqTitleInfo6.textContent = "insurance policy guarantees reimbursement of treatment costs in the event of an accident or illness, it will help when transporting home or in case of unforeseen circumstances, such as the loss of luggage, cancellation, and so Further.";
    faqTitle7.textContent = "Where can I get insurance?";
    faqTitleInfo7.textContent = "GROSS INSURANCE";
    faqTitle8.textContent = "Why do I need a bank account?";
    faqTitleInfo8.textContent = "if you want to get a visa as a foreign student or visa applicant, you will need to prove that you have sufficient funds. You can do it using a closed bank account.";
    faqTitle9.textContent = "Can I transfer?";
    faqTitleInfo9.textContent = "from any university in the top 1000 you can translate without an exam, in any other case translation is done through an exam.";
    faqTitle10.textContent = "Will the diploma be quoted in Uzbekistan?";
    faqTitleInfo10.textContent = "diploma of any foreign accredited university will be considered in Uzbekistan, subject to nostrification, and diplomas of the CIS countries pass without nostrification";
    faqTitle11.textContent = "Is it possible to pay for the contract in part?";
    faqTitleInfo11.textContent = "the contract can be paid in part, but if you make a payment immediately for a whole year, you can get discounts for 2-4 years learning.";
